How to configuring Git?

We need to configure git with the username and email id if we installed 
it for the first time.

To configure git for the first time in our local machine use the following git commands-

( NOTE: After installing git, it provides us with free command Line Interface(CLI)
i.e Git Bash. To run git command we can either use git bash or any other cli. 
i.e command prompt/terminal/VS code powershell)

git can also be configure locally in different projects using local keyward, just replace 
global with local.

git commands:- 
# To set username - git config --global user.name "My Name"
# To set email_ID - git config --global user.email "My email"

After we set our username and email we are good to start with git.

git commands to check details:
#To check username - git config user.name
#To check email    - git config user.email
#To check other details - git config --list


